> -----Original Message-----
> From: Jeff Garzik [mailto:jgarzik@mandrakesoft.com]
> > 
> >    With the latest kernel you can have the matrox driver 
> compiled with i2c
> > support without having i2c support in the kernel. This 
> causes the compile
> > to fail. This patch fixes this. It test to see if you have 
> i2c support
> > selected.
> 
> IMHO I2C is such a low-level bus, the user might not know to select it
> until it is too late.
> 
> Why not instead have 
> 
> 	define_tristate CONFIG_I2C $CONFIG_FB_MATROX
v4l is the same way.  If you forget to choose the right i2c (or don't choose
bit-banging), then it crashes on compile.  Well, at least last time I
compile in v4l this happened...
The above looks good.
